&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onboard and implement ADM for Addepar clients where you will lead the project management, solution design and execution of the implementation project&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with cross-functional teams to ensure successful project delivery and client satisfaction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize and context-switch effectively to lead simultaneous projects, seeing each through to the

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Addepar is a global data and AI platform empowering investment professionals to turn complex financial information into actionable intelligence. Addepar unifies portfolio, market and client data in a total portfolio view and delivers AI-powered insights within investment and client workflows. More than 1,400 firms in nearly 60 countries use Addepar to manage and advise on nearly $9 trillion in assets. Its open platform integrates with nearly 650 software, data and consulting partners to power end-to-end investment operations across firms of all sizes and complexity. Addepar supports clients worldwide with offices in New York City, Salt Lake City, London, Edinburgh, Pune, Dubai, Geneva, Singapore and São Paulo.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Addepar has just launched an Alternatives Product offering that gives Addepar clients the option to have their Private Funds data extracted, processed, validated, and ingested directly from Private Fund documents for a more automated end-to-end solution for handling Alternatives on the platform. This white-glove solution combines proprietary machine learning technology that automatically extracts data from Private Funds documents and human-in-loop review to validate any documents that fail to pass confidence and data quality checks.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the broader Addepar Data organization, the Alternatives Data Ops team is responsible for the human-in-loop review of Private Funds documents, ensuring clients’ Alternatives data is processed, validated, and available in Addepar in a timely manner. This role will include reviewing Private Fund statements, modifying data that has been incorrectly extracted by our machine learning models, and reprocessing the data within SLAs. The Alternatives Data Ops team plays a critical role in the success of Addepar’s Alternatives offering and requires daily communications with the Alternatives Product Team, Machine Learning Operations, clients, data providers (GPs and Fund Admins), and additional personnel across the organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-prosemirror-content-type=&quot;node&quot; data-prosemirror-node-name=&quot;paragraph&quot; data-prosemirror-node-block=&quot;true&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;Applicants must have legal authorization to work in the country where this role is based on the first day of employment. Visa sponsorship is not available for this position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Alternatives Data processing for Addepar clients, which includes but is not limited to:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting Private Fund statements (Capital Call Notices, Distribution Notices, and Capital Account Statements) processing exceptions captured by automated validation checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modifying document data that has been incorrectly extracted by our machine learning models to reflect the correct Private Fund transactions and valuations information contained in the Private Fund Statements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with our Machine Learning Operations team to identify and relabel documents for model retraining&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engaging clients, GPs, or Fund Admins to address statement data related inquiries and issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Onboard new clients to determine and establish the ownership structure of clients’ Private Fund positions within Addepar&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain Alternatives Data Operations workflow procedures and play-books&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Sales, Account Managers

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Addepar is a global data and AI platform empowering investment professionals to turn complex financial information into actionable intelligence. Addepar unifies portfolio, market and client data in a total portfolio view and delivers AI-powered insights within investment and client workflows. More than 1,400 firms in nearly 60 countries use Addepar to manage and advise on nearly $9 trillion in assets. Its open platform integrates with nearly 650 software, data and consulting partners to power end-to-end investment operations across firms of all sizes and complexity. Addepar supports clients worldwide with offices in New York City, Salt Lake City, London, Edinburgh, Pune, Dubai, Geneva, Singapore and São Paulo.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;The Role&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alts Data Operations is a newly launched Addepar team that focuses on Alternatives Investment Data.&amp;nbsp; The team collects and validates information on private funds, private companies and other non-public investments.&amp;nbsp; This data is used for our research projects on investment decision-making and deliver new research products on topics related to investing (e.g., briefs, working papers, journal articles, models). The R&amp;amp;I mission is to inform wealth managers and institutional investors on new ways to improve their investment performance, by helping them augment their governance, management, operations, and processes. The goal is to apply Addepar’s proprietary and private data (both quantitative and qualitative) to bring new and powerful insights to the world of investors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking an Alternatives Data Operations Analyst to join our growing presence in Edinburgh. This role will be dedicated to capturing and updating Alternatives data to power new innovations developed using a proprietary research platform. The platform aggregates over $7 Trillion in assets into an analytical data store that can be analyzed for new insights by researchers at Addepar and other prominent research institutions (e.g. London School of Economics, Dept. of Finance). The role is responsible for ensuring the platform has timely and high-quality data available. This will include oversight of the alternatives security master, data quality validations management, and workflow oversight.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have, and maintain, the right to work in the United Kingdom from the first day of employment. Please note that visa sponsorship is not available for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
